result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael A Demmith was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Armed Robbery [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court finds defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and Substance Abuse Program only after serving 4 years of confinement.

superMiscConds.notes: If a Wisconsin State Prison sentence is imposed, outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from all inmate money at a rate of 25% and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision.  If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with financial obligations owing, a judgment shall be entered.
Defendant shall not possess or use weapons.

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. 
Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with Julian T., Cheyenne H. or Benjamin L. 
Defendant shall not have contact with known gang members.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling or treatment programs as directed by his supervising agent. 
Defendant shall pay Dept of Corrections supervision fees.
Defendant shall obtain an HSED or GED.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
Defendant shall obtain and maintain full time employment or school or a combination thereof.
